== Deaths == * [[Tenbun]] 20th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1551]] {{ill|April 8|ja|4月8日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Oda Nobuhide|ja|織田信秀|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a military commander and father of Oda Nobunaga (born [[1510]]). * [[Keichō]] 4th year (leap March) ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1599]] {{ill|April 27|ja|4月27日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Maeda Toshiie|ja|前田利家|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a military commander and one of the Tairō; he was the first lord of the Kaga Domain (born [[1538]]). * 安政7th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1860 [[March 24|ja|3月24日]]) – {{ill|Ii Naosuke|ja|井伊直弼|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, Tairō of the Tokugawa shogunate (born [[1815]]). * 慶応4th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1868 [[March 26|ja|3月26日]]) – {{ill|Sagara Sōzō|ja|相楽総三|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a proponent of Sonnō jōi (born [[1839]]).
== Commemorations == * {{ill|Shōmiji|ja|上巳|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|Hina Matsuri|ja|雛祭り|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} * {{ill|Hama-ori|ja|浜下り|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} – In Okinawa, women purify themselves by presenting food in tiered boxes at the beach; this tradition is combined with clam digging. * 玄天上帝誕辰 – The birthday celebration of the Taoist deity {{ill|Xuantian Shangdi|ja|玄天上帝|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. * サームニエッショーサーム – A traditional event of the Zhuang people in China (in their language: samnyiedcosam) celebrating ancestral veneration with large-scale singing gatherings, also known as "三月初三." * An independent New Year celebration by the Khor Lao ethnic group in Vietnam.
