{{Lunisolar March}} '''March 3''' is the 3rd day of the month {{ill|March (Lunisolar)|ja|3月 (旧暦)|lt=March (Yayoi)|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, the 3rd month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} day is {{ill|Taian|ja|大安|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}.
== Events == * {{ill|Tenshō|ja|天正|1=Tenshō (Momoyama period)|lt=Tenshō Era|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 11th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1583]] {{ill|April 24|ja|4月24日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Toyotomi Hideyoshi|ja|羽柴秀吉|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} (later known as {{ill|Toyotomi Hideyoshi|ja|豊臣秀吉|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) captured {{ill|Kashida Katsuie|ja|柴田勝家|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}’s forces by taking {{ill|Ise Province|ja|伊勢|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}’s {{ill|Kameyama Castle|ja|亀山城 (伊勢国)|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} in a prelude to the {{ill|Battle of Shizugatake|ja|賤ヶ岳の戦い|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. * {{ill|Keichō|ja|慶長|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 8th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1603]] {{ill|April 14|ja|4月14日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – The {{ill|Nihonbashi|ja|日本橋|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} in Chūō, Tokyo, was opened. * {{ill|Kan'ei|ja|寛永|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 19th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1642]] {{ill|April 2|ja|4月2日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – The {{ill|Tokugawa shogunate|ja|徳川幕府|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} established the office of {{ill|Kanjō Bugyō|ja|勘定奉行|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. * {{ill|Kaei|ja|嘉永|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 7th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1854]] {{ill|March 31|ja|3月31日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – The Tokugawa shogunate and U.S. envoy Perry signed the {{ill|Nippon-America Treaty|ja|日米和親条約|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} (also known as the Kanagawa Treaty) in Yokohama, effectively ending national seclusion. * {{ill|Ansei|ja|安政|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 7th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1860]] {{ill|March 24|ja|3月24日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – During the [[Sakuradamon Incident|桜田門外の変]], Tairō {{ill|Ii Naosuke|ja|井伊直弼|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} was attacked and killed by rōnin (including Mito rōnin) outside Sakurada Gate of Edo Castle. * {{ill|Keiō|ja|慶応|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 4th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1868]] {{ill|March 26|ja|3月26日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – The Higashiyama Road Vanguard Government executed officials, including those of the [[Akahōtai|赤報隊]], as pseudo-officials.
== Births == * [[Shōō (Kamakura period)|Shōō]] 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1288]] {{ill|April 5|ja|4月5日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Later Fushimi Tennō|ja|後伏見天皇|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, the 93rd Emperor of Japan (died [[1336]]). * [[Tenbun]] 18th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1549]] {{ill|March 31|ja|3月31日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Tsuchi no Junkei|ja|筒井順慶|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a Sengoku daimyō (died [[1584]]). * {{ill|Kannen|ja|寛延|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 2nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1749]] {{ill|April 19|ja|4月19日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Ōta Nan-Ō|ja|大田南畝|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a playwright (died [[1823]]). * {{ill|Bunsei|ja|文政|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 8th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1825]] {{ill|April 20|ja|4月20日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Shiranui Kōuenemon|ja|不知火光右ヱ門|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, the 11th Yokozuna (died [[1879]]). * {{ill|Tenpō|ja|天保|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1832]] {{ill|April 3|ja|4月3日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Matsunomon Sansōko|ja|松の門三艸子|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a waka poet and geisha (died [[1914]]). * {{ill|Kaei|ja|嘉永|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 2nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1849]] {{ill|March 26|ja|3月26日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Hirata Tōsuke|ja|平田東助|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a bureaucrat and politician (died [[1925]]). * 嘉永4th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1851]] {{ill|April 4|ja|4月4日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Ogino Ginko|ja|荻野吟子|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a feminist and Japan’s first female doctor (died [[1913]]). * {{ill|Ansei|ja|安政|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 2nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1855]] {{ill|April 19|ja|4月19日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Sugiura Shigetake|ja|杉浦重剛|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a thinker and educator (died [[1924]]). * 安政6th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1859]] {{ill|April 5|ja|4月5日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Yasui Rimin|ja|安井理民|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, the founder of the first iteration of the Sōbu Railway (died [[1894]]). * [[Meiji era|Meiji]] 5th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1872]] {{ill|April 10|ja|4月10日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Itaya Hazan|ja|板谷波山|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a ceramic artist (died [[1963]]).
== Deaths == * [[Tenbun]] 20th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1551]] {{ill|April 8|ja|4月8日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Oda Nobuhide|ja|織田信秀|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a military commander and father of Oda Nobunaga (born [[1510]]). * [[Keichō]] 4th year (leap March) ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1599]] {{ill|April 27|ja|4月27日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Maeda Toshiie|ja|前田利家|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a military commander and one of the Tairō; he was the first lord of the Kaga Domain (born [[1538]]). * 安政7th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1860 [[March 24|ja|3月24日]]) – {{ill|Ii Naosuke|ja|井伊直弼|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, Tairō of the Tokugawa shogunate (born [[1815]]). * 慶応4th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1868 [[March 26|ja|3月26日]]) – {{ill|Sagara Sōzō|ja|相楽総三|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a proponent of Sonnō jōi (born [[1839]]).
== Commemorations == * {{ill|Shōmiji|ja|上巳|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|Hina Matsuri|ja|雛祭り|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} * {{ill|Hama-ori|ja|浜下り|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} – In Okinawa, women purify themselves by presenting food in tiered boxes at the beach; this tradition is combined with clam digging. * 玄天上帝誕辰 – The birthday celebration of the Taoist deity {{ill|Xuantian Shangdi|ja|玄天上帝|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. * サームニエッショーサーム – A traditional event of the Zhuang people in China (in their language: samnyiedcosam) celebrating ancestral veneration with large-scale singing gatherings, also known as "三月初三." * An independent New Year celebration by the Khor Lao ethnic group in Vietnam.
