== Events == * [[:en:Tenshō (Momoyama period)|Tenshō Era]] 11th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1583|1583]] [[:en:April 24|April 24]]) – {{ill|Toyotomi Hideyoshi|ja|羽柴秀吉|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Toyotomi Hideyoshi|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 豊臣秀吉}} (later known as [[:en:Toyotomi Hideyoshi|Toyotomi Hideyoshi]]) captured [[:en:Shibata Katsuie|Kashida Katsuie]]’s forces by taking [[:en:Ise|Ise Province]]’s [[:en:Kameyama Castle (Mie)|Kameyama Castle]] in a prelude to the [[:en:Battle of Shizugatake|Battle of Shizugatake]]. * [[:en:Keichō|Keichō]] 8th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1603|1603]] [[:en:April 14|April 14]]) – The [[:en:日本橋|Nihonbashi]] in Chūō, Tokyo, was opened. * [[:en:Kan'ei|Kan'ei]] 19th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1642|1642]] [[:en:April 2|April 2]]) – The {{ill|Tokugawa shogunate|ja|徳川幕府|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tokugawa shogunate|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 江戸幕府}} established the office of [[:en:Kanjō bugyō|Kanjō Bugyō]]. * [[:en:Kaei|Kaei]] 7th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1854|1854]] [[:en:March 31|March 31]]) – The Tokugawa shogunate and U.S. envoy Perry signed the [[:en:Convention of Kanagawa|Nippon-America Treaty]] (also known as the Kanagawa Treaty) in Yokohama, effectively ending national seclusion. * [[:en:Ansei|Ansei]] 7th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1860|1860]] [[:en:March 24|March 24]]) – During the [[:en:Sakuradamon Incident|桜田門外の変]], Tairō [[:en:Ii Naosuke|Ii Naosuke]] was attacked and killed by rōnin (including Mito rōnin) outside Sakurada Gate of Edo Castle. * [[:en:Keiō|Keiō]] 4th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1868|1868]] [[:en:March 26|March 26]]) – The Higashiyama Road Vanguard Government executed officials, including those of the [[Akahōtai|赤報隊]], as pseudo-officials.
== Births == * [[:en:Shōō (Kamakura period)|Shōō]] 1st year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1288|1288]] [[:en:April 5|April 5]]) – [[:en:Emperor Go-Fushimi|Later Fushimi Tennō]], the 93rd Emperor of Japan (died [[:en:1336|1336]]). * [[:en:Tenbun|Tenbun]] 18th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1549|1549]] [[:en:March 31|March 31]]) – [[:en:Tsutsui Junkei|Tsuchi no Junkei]], a Sengoku daimyō (died [[:en:1584|1584]]). * [[:en:Kan'en|Kannen]] 2nd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1749|1749]] [[:en:April 19|April 19]]) – [[:en:Ōta Nanpo|Ōta Nan-Ō]], a playwright (died [[:en:1823|1823]]). * [[:en:Bunsei|Bunsei]] 8th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1825|1825]] [[:en:April 20|April 20]]) – {{ill|Shiranui Kōuenemon|ja|不知火光右ヱ門|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shiranui Kōuenemon|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, the 11th Yokozuna (died [[:en:1879|1879]]). * [[:en:Tenpō|Tenpō]] 3rd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1832|1832]] [[:en:April 3|April 3]]) – {{ill|Matsunomon Sansōko|ja|松の門三艸子|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Matsunomon Sansōko|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, a waka poet and geisha (died [[:en:1914|1914]]). * [[:en:Kaei|Kaei]] 2nd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1849|1849]] [[:en:March 26|March 26]]) – [[:en:Hirata Tosuke|Hirata Tōsuke]], a bureaucrat and politician (died [[:en:1925|1925]]). * 嘉永4th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1851|1851]] [[:en:April 4|April 4]]) – [[:en:Ogino Ginko|Ogino Ginko]], a feminist and Japan’s first female doctor (died [[:en:1913|1913]]). * [[:en:Ansei|Ansei]] 2nd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1855|1855]] [[:en:April 19|April 19]]) – {{ill|Sugiura Shigetake|ja|杉浦重剛|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sugiura Shigetake|qq=}}, a thinker and educator (died [[:en:1924|1924]]). * 安政6th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1859|1859]] [[:en:April 5|April 5]]) – {{ill|Yasui Rimin|ja|安井理民|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yasui Rimin|qq=}}, the founder of the first iteration of the Sōbu Railway (died [[:en:1894|1894]]). * [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji]] 5th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1872|1872]] [[:en:April 10|April 10]]) – [[:en:Itaya Hazan|Itaya Hazan]], a ceramic artist (died [[:en:1963|1963]]).
== Deaths == * [[:en:Tenbun|Tenbun]] 20th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1551|1551]] [[:en:April 8|April 8]]) – [[:en:Oda Nobuhide|Oda Nobuhide]], a military commander and father of Oda Nobunaga (born [[:en:1510|1510]]). * [[:en:Keichō|Keichō]] 4th year (leap March) ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1599|1599]] [[:en:April 27|April 27]]) – [[:en:Maeda Toshiie|Maeda Toshiie]], a military commander and one of the Tairō; he was the first lord of the Kaga Domain (born [[:en:1538|1538]]). * 安政7th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] 1860 [[:en:March 24|ja|3月24日]]) – [[:en:Ii Naosuke|Ii Naosuke]], Tairō of the Tokugawa shogunate (born [[:en:1815|1815]]). * 慶応4th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] 1868 [[:en:March 26|ja|3月26日]]) – [[:en:Sagara Sōzō|Sagara Sōzō]], a proponent of Sonnō jōi (born [[:en:1839|1839]]).
== Commemorations == * [[:en:Double Third Festival|Shōmiji]] and [[:en:Hinamatsuri|Hina Matsuri]] * {{ill|Hama-ori|ja|浜下り|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hama-ori|qq=}} – In Okinawa, women purify themselves by presenting food in tiered boxes at the beach; this tradition is combined with clam digging. * 玄天上帝誕辰 – The birthday celebration of the Taoist deity [[:en:Xuanwu (god)|Xuantian Shangdi]]. * サームニエッショーサーム – A traditional event of the Zhuang people in China (in their language: samnyiedcosam) celebrating ancestral veneration with large-scale singing gatherings, also known as "三月初三." * An independent New Year celebration by the Khor Lao ethnic group in Vietnam.
